# build/nwp-server.deny-symbols — the fail-closed AI-free guarantee (ADR-0022/0024).
#
# Each non-comment line is an extended-regex (ERE), matched case-insensitively
# against the ASSEMBLED nwp-server artifact. ANY match fails the build. This is
# the mechanical form of ADR-0022's success metric: "a `strings` check returns
# zero matches for AI-vendor library symbols."
#
# The artifact is built from an ALLOWLIST (build/nwp-server.include), so this scan
# is defence in depth: it catches an AI/CI/SaaS reference that sneaks in via an
# allowlisted file (e.g. a shared lib that grew a SaaS client call).
#
# Self-hosted infra is NOT denied: the self-hosted git/artifact host, headscale,
# gotify, minisign, wireguard are all allowed. Only AI vendors, CI runners, and
# distrusted SaaS are.
#
# Granularity note (important): AI/CI tokens are matched BROADLY (bare vendor
# names) — those words have no legitimate place in this artifact. SaaS infra
# tokens are matched at the API/CLIENT SURFACE, not as bare words, because the
# legacy nwp.yml schema names its servers block `linode:` — so a bare `linode`
# would false-positive on every config-key read. nwp-server legitimately READS
# those keys (it must know how to reach prod); what it must never CONTAIN is the
# SaaS client itself (`lib/linode.sh`, an `api.linode.com` call, a token accessor).
# The allowlist remains the primary fail-closed guarantee; this list is the net.

# ── AI vendors / LLM clients ────────────────────────────────────────────────
anthropic
openai
\bclaude\b
\bollama\b
\bllm\b
agent-loop
\bcoder(s|-setup)?\b
claude-api

# ── CI runners / pipeline integration ───────────────────────────────────────
ci-stats
gitlab-ci
\.gitlab-ci
github/workflows

# ── Distrusted SaaS — matched at the API/client surface (see granularity note) ─
# Linode
api\.linode\.com
linode-cli
lib/linode\.sh
get_linode_token
# Cloudflare
api\.cloudflare\.com
lib/cloudflare\.sh
get_cloudflare_
# Backblaze B2 / object storage
backblazeb2
lib/b2\.sh
lib/storage\.sh
# Other distrusted SaaS (no config-key collision → bare names are safe)
twilio
gitlab\.com
github\.com
pushover
tailscale
sigstore
cosign
